---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Install — Theme Atoms" section="install">
  <header>
    <p class="kicker">Install</p>
    <h1>Install aish</h1>
    <p class="lead">aish is the shell that consumes theme-atoms. Themes work in any aish v0.2+ install.</p>
  </header>

  <h2>Homebrew (macOS / Linux)</h2>
  <pre><code>brew tap convergent-systems-co/tap
brew install aish</code></pre>

  <h2>Scoop (Windows)</h2>
  <pre><code>scoop bucket add csco https://github.com/convergent-systems-co/scoop-bucket
scoop install aish</code></pre>

  <h2>From source</h2>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/convergent-systems-co/aish.git
cd aish && go build ./cmd/aish</code></pre>

  <h2>Verify</h2>
  <pre><code>aish --version
aish theme list</code></pre>
  <p>If <code>theme list</code> shows at least <code>default</code>, you're ready.</p>

  <h2>Then</h2>
  <p><a href="/how-to-use">How to use →</a></p>

  <style>
    .kicker { color: var(--text-tertiary); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin: 0 0 4px; }
    .lead { color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 640px; }
    pre { max-width: 640px; }
  </style>
</Layout>
